<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="395" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,961,1413]" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,1116,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">Remarks.</emphasis>
Species widespread from Central Asia to the Mediterranean Region (
<bibRefCitation author="Kovar, I." box="[1217,1370,1116,1142]" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" pagination="568 - 630" refId="ref4244" refString="Kovar, I. (2007) Coccinellidae. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Smetana, A. (Eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera, Volume 4. Elateroidea, Derodontoidea, Bostrichoidea, Lymexyloidea, Cleroidea, Cucujoidea. Apollo Books, Stenstrup, pp. 71 - 74, 568 - 630." type="journal article" year="2007">Kovář 2007</bibRefCitation>
), but previously unrecorded from 
<collectingRegion box="[485,582,1155,1181]" country="Italy" name="Sardegna" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">Sardinia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Canepari, C." box="[598,777,1155,1181]" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" refId="ref3559" refString="Canepari, C. (2004) Fauna Europaea: Coccinellidae. In: Audisio, P. (Ed.), Fauna Europaea: Coleoptera 2, Beetles. Fauna Europaea version 1.1, available at http: // www. faunaeur. org [accessed September 2009 as version 1.3 of April 19 th 2007.]" type="url" year="2004">Canepari 2004</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,961,1413]" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Mulsant, 1850" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1850" box="[329,598,1194,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Diomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[329,420,1194,1219]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">Diomus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mulsant, E." box="[428,598,1194,1220]" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" pagination="451 - 1104" refId="ref4577" refString="Mulsant, E. (1850) Species des coleopteres trimeres securipalpes. Annales des Sciences Physiques et Naturelles, d'Agriculture et d'Industrie de Lyon (2), 2 (2), 451 - 1104." type="journal article" year="1850">Mulsant, 1850</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
once considered a subgenus of 
<taxonomicName authority="Mulsant, 1846" authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1846" box="[977,1243,1194,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Nephus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[977,1065,1194,1219]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">Nephus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Mulsant, E." box="[1073,1243,1194,1220]" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" refId="ref4545" refString="Mulsant, E. (1846) Histoire Naturelle des coleopteres de France. Sulcicolles - Securipalpes. Maison Libraire, Paris, XXIV + 280 pp. + 1 pl." type="book" year="1846">Mulsant, 1846</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by postcoxal lines united with the posterior margin of the first abdominal sternum. Subsequently 
<bibRefCitation author="Gordon, R. D." pageId="1" pageNumber="395" pagination="1 - 219" refId="ref4081" refString="Gordon, R. D. (1999) South American Coccinellidae (Coleoptera), Part VI: a systematic revision of the South American Diomini, new tribe (Scymninae). Annales Zoologici, 49 (Suppl. 1), 1 - 219." type="journal article" year="1999">Gordon (1999)</bibRefCitation>
raised 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mulsant" authorityYear="1850" box="[315,406,1272,1297]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Diomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[315,406,1272,1297]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">Diomus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to genus level and created the tribe 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon" authorityYear="1999" box="[835,933,1271,1297]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Diomini">Diomini</taxonomicName>
based on the shape of the basal capsule of the sipho and the morphology of the basal lobe. In 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Motshulsky" baseAuthorityYear="1837" box="[755,943,1310,1335]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Diomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubidus">
<emphasis box="[755,943,1310,1335]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">Diomus rubidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the basal capsule of the sipho is identical to many species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Dobzhansky 1928" authorityName="Dobzhansky" authorityYear="1928" box="[381,738,1348,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Scymniscus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[381,516,1349,1374]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">Scymniscus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Dobzhansky, Th." box="[524,738,1348,1374]" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" pagination="116 - 123" refId="ref3765" refString="Dobzhansky, Th. (1928) Die Coccinelliden von Gouvernement Semipalatinsk. Revue Russe d'Entomologie, 22 (1 - 2), 116 - 123. [In Russian with descriptions in Latin.]" type="journal article" year="1928">Dobzhansky 1928</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis box="[756,777,1349,1374]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="395">cf</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Canepari, C." box="[793,967,1348,1374]" pageId="1" pageNumber="395" pagination="49 - 62" refId="ref3466" refString="Canepari, C. (2000) The Nephus subgenus Sidis in Italy (Coleoptera Coccinellidae). Bollettino della Societa Entomologica Italiana, 132 (1), 49 - 62." type="journal article" year="2000">Canepari 2000</bibRefCitation>
) with short sipho and basal capsule not T-shaped.
</paragraph>
